The paper deals with a privacy-preserving algorithm for packing problems, which involves designing efficient algorithms for resource allocation. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) to achieve differential privacy. The focus on optimizing the trade-off between privacy and efficiency suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the security implications of the algorithm, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of game theory (cs.GT).
